# Introduction
The Gefieder image is multi-tenant / team data analytics platform built on top of 
PostgreSQL, DuckDB, SQLMesh and Django (with Unfold admin interface).


## Instructions

Build the image from the repository root:

```bash
podman build -t gefieder .
```

Run the container with the application and PostgreSQL exposed:

```bash
podman run -d \
  --name gefieder \
  --replace \
  -p 8000:8000 \
  -p 5432:5432 \
  -e POSTGRES_PASSWORD=duckdb \
  gefieder
```

If the container is already using the same ports, stop or remove the old one first:

```bash
podman rm -f gefieder
```

Connect to the running services:

- Open the Django application at http://localhost:8000/
- Connect to PostgreSQL with:

```bash
psql -h localhost -p 5432 -U postgres -d postgres
```

When prompted for a password, use the same value that was passed as POSTGRES_PASSWORD (for example, `duckdb`).